title: 1995 Players Championship
text:
The 1995 Players Championship was a <a href="golf">golf</a> tournament in <a href="Florida">Florida</a> on the <a href="PGA%20Tour">PGA Tour</a>, held at <a href="TPC%20Sawgrass">TPC Sawgrass</a> in <a href="Ponte%20Vedra%20Beach%2C%20Florida">Ponte Vedra Beach</a>, southeast of <a href="Jacksonville%2C%20Florida">Jacksonville</a>. It was the 22nd <a href="The%20Players%20Championship">Players Championship</a>. 
On a wind-dried course, <a href="Lee%20Janzen">Lee Janzen</a> won at 283 (−5), a stroke ahead of runner-up <a href="Bernhard%20Langer">Bernhard Langer</a>. Janzen sank a putt for par on the final hole for the win. 
Defending champion <a href="Greg%20Norman">Greg Norman</a> finished eleven strokes back, in a tie for 37th place.
Venue.
This was the fourteenth Players Championship held at the TPC at Sawgrass Stadium Course, and it remained at .
